  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the optimal site for application of local
      anesthetics in total knee arthroplasty surgery. The hypothesis is, that improved pain relief
      is obtained when administering local anesthetics in the tissues sourrounding the knee joint
      compared to the knee joint itself.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
